# Tushar Bhandarkar — AI Portfolio
# Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
Personal portfolio website for an AI practitioner. Static site built with Next.js 16, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and Framer Motion. Deployable to Vercel via `npm run build` → `out/` directory.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16+ with App Router, `output: 'export'` (static)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode — never use `any`)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with CSS variables
- **Animation**: Framer Motion (`useInView` for scroll triggers)
- **Icons**: Lucide React (no `Github`/`Linkedin` — use `src/components/ui/SocialIcons.tsx`)
- **Fonts**: Playfair Display (display/serif) + Lato (body) via `next/font/google`

## Design System — Nature-Inspired Editorial

### Colors (always use these exact values)
```
Background:       #0D1A0F   (deep forest)
Surface/Cards:    #162418   (forest surface)
Surface-2:        #1E2F20
Accent green:     #4A7C59   (moss green) — primary CTAs, completed states
Accent hover:     #3d6b4a
Gold:             #C9A84C   — labels, logo dot, section eyebrows, ornaments
Text primary:     #F0EBE0   (warm cream)
Text secondary:   #9A9080   (warm sand/muted)
Border:           rgba(201,168,76,0.10)  — standard
Border strong:    rgba(201,168,76,0.25)  — hover/active
Gold muted bg:    rgba(201,168,76,0.07)  — badge backgrounds
```

### Typography
- **Display headings**: `style={{ fontFamily: "var(--font-display, Playfair Display, serif)" }}` — use `italic` and `font-bold`
- **Section eyebrows**: `text-xs font-medium text-[#C9A84C] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]`
- **Body text**: `text-[#9A9080] leading-[1.85]`
- **Primary text**: `text-[#F0EBE0]`

### Component Patterns
- **Cards**: `bg-[#162418] border border-[rgba(201,168,76,0.10)] rounded-[12px]`
- **Hover glow**: `hover:border-[rgba(201,168,76,0.30)] hover:shadow-[0_0_24px_rgba(74,124,89,0.10)]`
- **Badges (muted)**: `bg-[rgba(201,168,76,0.07)] text-[#9A9080] border border-[rgba(201,168,76,0.12)]`
- **Badges (accent)**: `bg-[#4A7C59]/15 text-[#7ab890] border border-[#4A7C59]/30`
- **Badges (gold)**: `bg-[rgba(201,168,76,0.12)] text-[#C9A84C] border border-[rgba(201,168,76,0.25)]`
- **Inputs**: `bg-[#162418] border border-[rgba(201,168,76,0.10)] focus:border-[rgba(201,168,76,0.35)]`

### Ornamental details (nature-editorial feel)
- Gold `✦` dividers between elements
- Top/bottom section hairlines: `bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[rgba(201,168,76,0.2)] to-transparent`
- Subtle grid overlay in hero: `opacity-[0.025]`, 80px cell size

## File Structure
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx         # Fonts, metadata, JSON-LD
│   ├── page.tsx           # Composes all 9 sections
│   └── globals.css        # CSS variables + base styles
├── components/
│   ├── ui/
│   │   ├── Button.tsx     # variants: primary (green), outline, ghost, gold
│   │   ├── Card.tsx       # glow prop for hover state
│   │   ├── Badge.tsx      # variants: accent, muted, gold
│   │   ├── ProgressBar.tsx # animated on scroll
│   │   └── SocialIcons.tsx # GithubIcon, LinkedinIcon (SVG — lucide has no social icons)
│   ├── sections/          # Hero, About, Timeline, Projects, Skills, Resume, Roadmap, Contact
│   └── layout/            # Navbar, Footer
├── data/
│   ├── projects.ts        # Add projects here — one object per project
│   ├── skills.ts          # Skill categories + levels (0-100)
│   └── timeline.ts        # 6-month journey nodes
├── hooks/
│   ├── useInView.ts       # Re-exports Framer Motion useInView
│   └── useScrollProgress.ts
└── lib/utils.ts           # cn() helper
```

## Code Conventions
- **No inline styles** except `fontFamily` for display font variable
- **All content in `src/data/`** — never hardcode content in components
- **Framer Motion animations**: always use `useInView` with `{ once: true, margin: "-60px" }` for scroll triggers
- **Section eyebrows**: always `text-xs font-medium text-[#C9A84C] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]` + `mb-2`
- **Section headings**: always add `italic` class + `style={{ fontFamily: "var(--font-display...)" }}`
- **Stagger animations**: use `delay: index * 0.1` pattern for grid items
- **No `any` types** — write proper TypeScript interfaces
- **No comments** unless the WHY is non-obvious

## Adding a New Project
Edit `src/data/projects.ts` — add one object to the array:
```ts
{
  id: "unique-id",
  title: "Project Title",
  description: "What it does.",
  tools: ["Claude", "Zapier"],
  link: "https://...",
  featured: true, // optional
}
```

## Deployment
```bash
npm run build   # → out/ directory (static export)
vercel --prod   # or push to GitHub → auto-deploy on Vercel
```

## DO NOT
- Use `any` TypeScript type
- Add inline styles (except font-family variable)
- Use `Github` or `Linkedin` from lucide-react (not exported — use SocialIcons.tsx)
- Hardcode content in components (use src/data/ files)
- Use blue `#2563EB` anywhere — this design uses green `#4A7C59` + gold `#C9A84C`
- Create new data files without updating the section component that reads them
